## REQ-BFF-005: CLI Command Integration

### Scenario: bff:init creates new project
```gherkin
Given the user runs `mfe bff:init my-bff --specs ./api.yaml`
Then a new directory my-bff is created
  And package.json includes Mesh dependencies
  And server.ts template is generated
  And Dockerfile template is generated
```

### Scenario: bff:init adds to existing project
```gherkin
Given an existing MFE project directory
  And the directory contains mfe-manifest.yaml
When the user runs `mfe bff:init` (no name argument)
Then Mesh dependencies are added to package.json
  And server.ts is created in the project
  And existing files are not overwritten
```

### Scenario: bff:validate checks configuration
```gherkin
Given a mfe-manifest.yaml with valid data: section
When the user runs `mfe bff:validate`
Then each source is validated
  And local OpenAPI spec paths are checked for existence
  And a success message is displayed
```

### Scenario: bff:validate catches invalid transform
```gherkin
Given a mfe-manifest.yaml with unknown transform type
When the user runs `mfe bff:validate`
Then a warning is displayed for the unknown transform
```

### Scenario: bff:dev starts development server
```gherkin
Given a project with valid BFF configuration
When the user runs `mfe bff:dev`
Then .meshrc.yaml is extracted from DSL
  And mesh dev process is started
  And GraphQL playground is available
```

